Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees. Remove the stalks from the centre of the @Portobello Mushrooms{4}. Pick the @Flat Leaf Parsley{5} leaves from their stalks. Discard the stalks and roughly chop the leaves. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{4}(peeled) (you can use a #garlic press{} if you have one!). Melt, but don't brown, your @Netherend Butter Salted{1.5%bun}.

> If you have a microwave, pop the butter in a bowl and melt in the microwave for 30 seconds.

In a #bowl{}, mix the @Panko Breadcrumbs{50%g} with the chopped parsley, melted butter and half the garlic. Season with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @ground black pepper{}. Fill the mushrooms with this filling and place on a #baking tray{}. Cook in the oven for ~{15%minutes} or until the breadcrumbs are nice and golden.

== Stew ==

Now for the stew! Peel and finely chop the @Red Onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped). Chop the ends off the @Courgette{1}, cut in half lengthways, then again lengthways to create four long strips. Roughly chop each long strip into chunks at 1cm intervals. Pick the @Basil{3} leaves and set aside for later. Drain the @Organic Cannellini Beans{1%400g can} in a #colander{} and rinse under cold water.

Add @olive oil{3%tbsp} to a #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the red onion and sweat for ~{5%minutes} or until the onions are translucent. Add the courgettes and cook for another ~{10%minutes}. Season with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @ground black pepper{} and then add the remaining garlic. Cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1} and bring the stew to the boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and simmer for ~{8%minutes} or until the sauce has reduced by a third. Add the cannellini beans and cook for another ~{1%minute}. Just before serving, tear and stir in the basil leaves.

Serve the mushrooms on top of a generous bowlful of the stew and enjoy!